body_html:
Looks like the //tensorflow/tools/api/tests:api_compatibility_test is also failing, caused by

ERROR:tensorflow:2 differences found between API and golden.
ERROR:tensorflow:Issue 1        : New object tensorflow.nn.rnn_cell.SRUCell found (added).
ERROR:tensorflow:Issue 2        : Change detected in python object: tensorflow.nn.rnn_cell.

The issue is from another PR #13978 which introduced the SRU implementation.

It seems that tensorflow/core/api_def/update_api_def.sh only adds the ops in c++ but does not update in golden.

I run with

bazel-bin/tensorflow/tools/api/tests/api_compatibility_test \
          --update_goldens True

and the issue seems to be fixed.

Pushed though to the PR, though not sure this is the right fix as I am not familiar with the API changes.

body:
Looks like the `//tensorflow/tools/api/tests:api_compatibility_test` is also failing, caused by
```
ERROR:tensorflow:2 differences found between API and golden.
ERROR:tensorflow:Issue 1        : New object tensorflow.nn.rnn_cell.SRUCell found (added).
ERROR:tensorflow:Issue 2        : Change detected in python object: tensorflow.nn.rnn_cell.
```

The issue is from another PR #13978 which introduced the SRU implementation.

It seems that `tensorflow/core/api_def/update_api_def.sh` only adds the ops in c++ but does not update in golden.

I run with
```
bazel-bin/tensorflow/tools/api/tests/api_compatibility_test \
          --update_goldens True
```

and the issue seems to be fixed.

Pushed though to the PR, though not sure this is the right fix as I am not familiar with the API changes.
